**File: `stats_models/src/lib.rs:664` – Incorrect statistical formulas in `GlmFit::summary`**
The `summary` implementation for `GlmFit` calculates goodness-of-fit statistics (R-squared, F-statistic) using formulas appropriate for Ordinary Least Squares (OLS) linear models, not for Generalised Linear Models (GLMs). This is statistically incorrect and will produce misleading results for any non-Gaussian family. For example, it uses Residual Sum of Squares (RSS) instead of deviance for key calculations.

