In `Lm::fit_internal`, rank deficiency is handled by checking if any computed coefficient is excessively large (`> 1e10`). This is a heuristic that may not be robust. A more principled approach is to use the rank and permutation matrix from the column-pivoted QR decomposition to identify and zero out coefficients corresponding to linearly dependent columns.

